Chapter 4

WAVEGUIDES - DEVICES

QUICK FEM (C) 1997 G.PELOSI R. COCCIOLI S. SELLERI


  Directory Contents:

 +-- EHDEV.FOR       Main program
 +-- EHD_SUBS.FOR    Subroutines
 |
 +-- PSHIFT -+- The waveguide problem, or a fixed phase shifter
 |           |
 |           +-- PSHIFT#.TXT   Mesh description file, being # the number of
 |           |                 element sides used in the discretization along
 |           |                 the waveguide axis (axis z)
 |           +-- PSHIFT#.FEM   The relative meshes
 |           +-- PSHIFT.AUX    The electromagnetic data file, which is the same 
 |           |                 for all the examples
 |           +-- PSHIFT#.OUT   THe relative outputs
 |           +-- PSHIFT#.GNU   Filtered output containing only the fundamental
 |           |                 mode, ready for plotting
 |           +-- PSHIFT.REF    Reference file, with the analitic solution
 |
 +-- IRIS -+- A simple symmetric iris
 |         |
 |         +-- IRIS1.TXT    The mesh description file
 |         +-- IRIS1.FEM    The relative mesh
 |         +-- IRIS1_#.AUX  The electromagnetic data files, for # number
 |         |                of modes at each port.
 |         +-- IRIS1_#.OUT  The relative outputs
 |         +-- IRIS1_#.GNU  Filtered output, again ready for plotting 
 |         +-- S##_%%.GNU   Filtered output, to show modal amplitudes, at
 |                          port ## and frequency %%GHz
 |
 +-- BEND -+- Various bend shapes in WR75, E or H plane
           |
           +-- BEND$?.TXT The mesh desription file, being $ a letter to
           |              distinguish bend shape:
           |
           |                q - square
           |                f - fully mitered
           |                p - partially mitered
           |                c - circular
           |     
           |              And ? a letter to distinguish the plane (E or H)
           |
           +-- BEND$?.FEM The relative meshes
           +-- BEND?.AUX  The auxiliary mesh description file, plane E or H
           +-- BEND$?.OUT The output files
           +-- BEND$?.GNU The filtered outputs


